Defendant Darrell L Wyatt in court with Attorney Kerri Terann Cleghorn.  Defendant Darrell L Wyatt in custody.  Margaret Anne Kunisch appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Presentence report reviewed.  No corrections.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court imposed the following sentence:  The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be EIGHT (8) years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for FIVE (5) years with credit for THREE HUNDRED NINETY-THREE (393) days time served.  Defendant shall serve THREE (3) years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.  

The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program;
The defendant is eligible for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  

The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - Restitution in the amount of $561.81 to victim, Erik V.  This is to be paid BEFORE costs and surcharges.
 - Pay the DNA surcharge, costs and disbursements. Court ordered for every $10 the Defendant has on his books, $1 is to towards restitution.  Balance would be then be paid while on Extended Supervision.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

